WEBVTT

00:01.034 --> 00:02.936
REBECCA: Previously
on The Practice:

00:02.969 --> 00:05.038
I have a good portion
of the money.

00:05.071 --> 00:06.406
You're two weeks late now.

00:06.740 --> 00:09.242
I'm gonna borrow some money
from my retirement account.

00:09.275 --> 00:10.511
My proposal is this--

00:10.544 --> 00:12.312
you provide
some legal services,

00:12.345 --> 00:13.980
and your debt goes away.

00:14.014 --> 00:15.849
The guy's my bookie.
What do you owe?

00:15.882 --> 00:17.350
Twenty-seven thousand.

00:17.383 --> 00:19.920
His ex-wife is suing him
for fraud.

00:19.953 --> 00:20.821
He won the lottery,

00:20.854 --> 00:23.356
she's claiming he didn't
tell her.

00:23.389 --> 00:27.127
I get 70,
and you get 30.

00:27.160 --> 00:28.629
(camera shutter clicking)

00:28.895 --> 00:30.731
You believe this?
They think I whacked her.

00:30.764 --> 00:33.800
Did you?
Check my alibi,
you want peace of mind.

00:33.834 --> 00:34.968
Did you have it done?

00:35.001 --> 00:36.770
All right, just get me out.

00:36.803 --> 00:39.506
Your wife's estate
can still make a claim.

00:39.540 --> 00:40.841
Do you want me
to follow up on that?

00:40.874 --> 00:45.111
No. Think I might engage
new counsel, just the same.

00:45.145 --> 00:47.380
So I guess we're done, then.

00:47.413 --> 00:49.716
You still owe me
the 27, Jimmy.

00:49.750 --> 00:51.417
Didn't exactly
work that off.

00:51.451 --> 00:53.720
What do you say you walk
out the door,

00:53.754 --> 00:56.790
forget my debt,
and I'll forget

00:56.823 --> 00:58.992
how you threatened
to kill your wife?

00:59.025 --> 01:01.461
The truth is
I got more on you

01:01.494 --> 01:02.796
than you got on me.

01:03.830 --> 01:05.498
I'm asking you...

01:05.532 --> 01:08.034
to get out of this office, now.

01:09.369 --> 01:12.005
I need that money.
I'll give you a week.

01:18.779 --> 01:20.514
I can't even believe
they're letting him out.

01:20.547 --> 01:22.182
He's managed to convince
the shrinks

01:22.215 --> 01:23.684
he's no longer a danger.

01:26.019 --> 01:27.554
Remember, he was never
actually charged

01:27.588 --> 01:29.756
in the kidnapping
of your son.

01:29.790 --> 01:32.626
The police know he did it.
They just couldn't prove it.

01:32.659 --> 01:35.061
Plus he's a convicted
child molester.

01:35.095 --> 01:37.030
Don't these people
repeat their crimes?

01:38.131 --> 01:40.767
What exactly are you
hiring me to do?

01:40.801 --> 01:42.068
To try to keep him in jail?

01:43.804 --> 01:44.671
We want to bury our son.

01:44.705 --> 01:46.807
Only he knows
where the body is.

01:48.308 --> 01:49.610
If there even
still is one.

01:51.344 --> 01:55.582
We were wondering
if we could somehow

01:55.616 --> 01:58.184
force him to tell us
where the remains are.

01:58.218 --> 01:59.452
I really don't see how.

02:00.687 --> 02:02.088
If he were to tell us
where the body is,

02:02.122 --> 02:04.357
he'd effectively be
admitting to the murder.

02:04.390 --> 02:05.992
We're told you have
a relationship

02:06.026 --> 02:07.961
with the DA's office.

02:07.994 --> 02:09.562
Could you--
We were thinking

02:09.596 --> 02:12.866
if you could get them
to consider filing charges

02:12.899 --> 02:14.200
against Pierce
for the kidnapping,

02:14.234 --> 02:17.437
that would give you
some leverage, wouldn't it?

02:17.470 --> 02:18.739
Maybe we could
make some deal.

02:18.772 --> 02:21.107
I know you've been
to the DA's office,

02:21.141 --> 02:22.876
and I know what
they've told you.

02:22.909 --> 02:25.311
Because we're just two
anonymous people,

02:25.345 --> 02:27.681
walking in off the street.
They know you.

02:27.714 --> 02:29.349
If you asked--
Mr. Baldwin,

02:29.382 --> 02:32.218
first of all,
this kidnapping happened

02:32.252 --> 02:35.188
eighteen years ago.

02:35.221 --> 02:37.524
If they couldn't
build a case then,
there's no way.

02:43.630 --> 02:45.265
I think you have to
let it go now.

02:46.432 --> 02:48.168
We can't let it go.

02:50.303 --> 02:51.838
We need to bury our son.

03:02.315 --> 03:05.318
(music playing)

03:53.834 --> 03:55.201
Wrongful death?

03:55.235 --> 03:58.071
For a murder that took place
18 years ago?

03:58.104 --> 04:00.173
It's a long shot.
ELLENOR: What's the end game?

04:00.707 --> 04:03.043
Even if you do win,
does he have any assets?

04:03.076 --> 04:04.277
It's not about money.

04:04.310 --> 04:05.411
Then what's it about?

04:05.445 --> 04:07.848
The parents want
to bury their son.

04:07.881 --> 04:08.949
They want closure.

04:08.982 --> 04:10.951
If I can create the threat
of a lawsuit,

04:10.984 --> 04:12.352
maybe we can get this guy
to reveal

04:12.385 --> 04:13.520
where the remains are.

04:14.888 --> 04:16.923
Forgive me. I don't mean
to be insensitive,

04:16.957 --> 04:20.493
but suppose you do succeed--
what's our contingency?

04:20.527 --> 04:22.128
Lindsay, try to get
the police records.

04:22.162 --> 04:25.331
Find out whatever
the DA's office has, or had.

04:25.566 --> 04:27.834
Ellenor, research the statute
of limitations issue.

04:27.868 --> 04:29.703
That'll definitely
be challenged.

04:29.736 --> 04:31.772
Rebecca, you and Jimmy
get started on the complaint.

04:32.606 --> 04:33.674
Where is Jimmy?

04:37.143 --> 04:38.278
Thanks.

04:41.014 --> 04:44.918
Jimmy, jeez.
How long's it been?

04:44.951 --> 04:46.052
Aunt Maria's funeral.

04:46.319 --> 04:48.922
Oh, too long.
You put on weight.

04:48.955 --> 04:53.560
Yeah, and you're like this
big fat cat yourself now.

04:53.594 --> 04:56.563
Parking lot king.
Yeah, king.

04:56.597 --> 04:59.666
I barely got
a one and a quarter percent
profit margin going here.

05:02.803 --> 05:03.904
What's up, Jim?

05:05.471 --> 05:07.007
Uh, well...

05:08.174 --> 05:09.643
We're family.

05:09.676 --> 05:11.645
Uh, I've gotten myself

05:11.678 --> 05:14.781
into a little bit
of a financial jam.

05:14.815 --> 05:16.449
Normal circumstances,

05:16.482 --> 05:18.118
I would never hit you up
for a loan.

05:18.151 --> 05:21.054
Normal circumstances,
I'd give it to you.

05:22.255 --> 05:23.189
Problem is, Jimmy,

05:23.223 --> 05:25.959
I just had to write
a sizeable check myself,

05:25.992 --> 05:27.561
so it's gonna depend
on how big

05:27.594 --> 05:29.963
your little bit of a jam is.

05:29.996 --> 05:32.165
I'm feeling sick
to my stomach just asking.

05:33.099 --> 05:34.334
You owe your book.

05:37.170 --> 05:39.840
I keep tabs.
You're family.

05:39.873 --> 05:42.208
Plus, I like the ponies myself.

05:42.509 --> 05:43.409
How much?

05:43.443 --> 05:45.912
It's more football than--
How much?

05:47.848 --> 05:49.049
Twenty-seven grand.

05:51.051 --> 05:52.252
Jimmy.

05:53.720 --> 05:56.723
I wish I could help you,
but, uh,

05:56.757 --> 05:58.491
the timing's just not good.

06:05.532 --> 06:06.667
Hey, listen...

06:07.568 --> 06:10.837
Listen, I got a tip on a horse

06:10.871 --> 06:12.472
running at Suffolk
day after tomorrow.

06:12.506 --> 06:13.339
He's a sure winner.

06:13.373 --> 06:16.176
I've bet on too many
sure winners, Dom.

06:16.209 --> 06:17.644
How I got in this mess.

06:18.979 --> 06:22.616
Well, like I said,
I wish I could help.

06:26.720 --> 06:29.923
I'm going to serve him
with the complaint myself.

06:29.956 --> 06:31.825
Now, listen,
you'll have to sign

06:31.858 --> 06:34.327
a confidentiality agreement.

06:34.360 --> 06:35.696
Why?
Because there's no way

06:35.729 --> 06:37.063
he's gonna tell us
where the body is

06:37.097 --> 06:39.633
if he thinks you'll go
running to the police.

06:39.666 --> 06:41.702
This isn't about that.
I understand.

06:41.735 --> 06:44.470
But he'll obviously need
to be convinced.

06:44.505 --> 06:47.340
We will give him
whatever he wants.

06:47.373 --> 06:49.209
Just tell us
where Chad is.

06:50.110 --> 06:51.244
You'll agree
not to pursue him

06:51.277 --> 06:52.946
civilly or criminally.

06:52.979 --> 06:54.314
We understand.

06:54.581 --> 06:56.917
May I go with you?
To the prison?

06:57.117 --> 06:59.720
I don't think
that's a great idea.

06:59.753 --> 07:03.557
A mother's plea might--
This is not about a plea,
Mrs. Baldwin.

07:04.290 --> 07:06.727
This is a threat.

07:06.760 --> 07:08.261
Better it come
from a lawyer.

07:11.832 --> 07:13.099
Are you serious?

07:13.133 --> 07:14.901
I'm just asking you
to check it out.

07:14.935 --> 07:17.638
Lindsay, a kidnapping
that happened 18 years ago,

07:17.671 --> 07:19.540
I can promise you
it's inactive.

07:19.573 --> 07:21.374
I'd just like you to review
the file if you could...

07:21.407 --> 07:22.976
Assuming I can
even find it.

07:23.009 --> 07:24.678
...and tell me
what you have.

07:25.779 --> 07:26.980
Please.

07:31.117 --> 07:32.018
I just want to make sure

07:32.052 --> 07:33.887
you've truly considered
the ramifications

07:33.920 --> 07:37.423
of closing out
your IRA.
I have.

07:37.457 --> 07:39.025
Realizing that you'll
be liable

07:39.059 --> 07:40.927
for taxes
on the entire amount.

07:40.961 --> 07:42.228
Realizing that.

07:43.930 --> 07:47.100
Also realizing you'll pay
a fairly onerous penalty

07:47.133 --> 07:48.502
for early withdrawal.

07:48.535 --> 07:50.370
Also realizing.

07:50.403 --> 07:52.138
Do you own a house?
Because we offer
a wide variety

07:52.172 --> 07:54.074
of home equity products--
Look.

07:54.107 --> 07:55.642
Maybe I ought to be committed.

07:55.676 --> 07:57.410
But this is what I want to do.

07:58.579 --> 07:59.880
If you insist. It's just--

07:59.913 --> 08:01.314
I'm a renter.

08:02.348 --> 08:04.618
How much will I get
from the IRA?

08:06.853 --> 08:08.421
(sighs)

08:13.059 --> 08:14.661
Approximately $8,200.

08:16.129 --> 08:17.998
Eighty-two hundred?

08:18.031 --> 08:20.233
My retirement fund
is $8,200?

08:20.266 --> 08:22.468
You're 23 years shy
of retirement age.

08:22.503 --> 08:24.437
With your maximum
annual contribution,

08:24.470 --> 08:25.906
if you left this
current amount intact--

08:25.939 --> 08:27.373
just give me the money.

08:33.947 --> 08:38.885
Look, I had nothing to do with
that Baldwin kid going missing.

08:38.919 --> 08:41.121
It wasn't me.

08:41.154 --> 08:43.289
You'll need a lawyer.

08:43.323 --> 08:44.991
If the trial starts
before you're released,

08:45.025 --> 08:47.794
you'll be transported
to and from court.

08:47.828 --> 08:49.763
They never even arrested me.

08:49.796 --> 08:51.932
You know why?
Because I didn't do it.

08:51.965 --> 08:54.234
Like you never molested
those three little boys

08:54.267 --> 08:55.669
who put you in here?

08:59.740 --> 09:00.841
You married?

09:02.976 --> 09:05.378
Is that a threat,
Mr. Pierce?

09:05.411 --> 09:07.347
No, it's not a threat.

09:07.380 --> 09:10.517
Look, she gotta be here
for this?
Yes, she does.

09:10.551 --> 09:12.252
I need a witness.

09:12.553 --> 09:16.523
I asked if you're married.
I see the ring on your finger.

09:16.557 --> 09:19.492
You probably got
a nice wife.

09:19.526 --> 09:24.798
You feel like getting it off,
she's who you probably think of.

09:24.831 --> 09:27.701
You got fantasies
about other women,
that's cool.

09:27.734 --> 09:30.103
Everybody understands,
am I right?

09:30.136 --> 09:32.405
What are you
talking about?

09:32.438 --> 09:34.340
I'm explaining something.

09:36.042 --> 09:39.946
Nobody on the planet can help
who they're attracted to.

09:39.980 --> 09:41.147
For me...

09:42.949 --> 09:44.951
...it was always little boys.

09:46.219 --> 09:48.021
I fooled myself
into thinking

09:48.054 --> 09:51.157
it was okay,
it didn't hurt anybody,
not really.

09:54.460 --> 09:56.296
I did some bad things.

09:58.431 --> 09:59.633
I admit it.

10:01.367 --> 10:02.836
And I got to live with that.

10:04.470 --> 10:06.072
So do all the boys
you hurt.

10:07.040 --> 10:09.710
Yeah, and I gotta
live with that, too.

10:13.413 --> 10:16.382
But I had nothing to do
with your clients' kid,

10:16.416 --> 10:18.451
and they got no right
to sue me.

10:19.620 --> 10:23.123
I could probably get them
to drop the suit.

10:23.156 --> 10:26.827
They just want to know
where their son is.

10:26.860 --> 10:31.231
I don't know what happened
to that kid.

10:39.005 --> 10:40.707
Have your attorney call me.

10:51.685 --> 10:54.254
He denied it?
Yes.

10:54.287 --> 10:56.489
Did he deny molesting
those other boys?

10:56.523 --> 10:57.558
No.

10:58.959 --> 11:00.961
But he said he didn't
kidnap your son.

11:03.363 --> 11:04.798
So what happens now?

11:04.831 --> 11:08.234
He retained a lawyer.
A good one.

11:08.268 --> 11:11.337
She filed an immediate motion
for summary judgment.

11:11.371 --> 11:13.139
We go and argue that next.

11:13.173 --> 11:14.908
If we can get by that,

11:14.941 --> 11:18.244
we can at least have
some leverage to make him talk.

11:22.448 --> 11:24.618
BOBBY: So I'll meet you
at the courthouse at 10:00.

11:24.651 --> 11:26.219
Okay.
Thank you.

11:27.521 --> 11:28.855
Good night.

11:31.357 --> 11:32.859
Hey, Jimmy.

11:34.595 --> 11:35.696
Hi.

11:37.998 --> 11:39.600
Everything squared away
with your bookie?

11:39.800 --> 11:40.667
The last I heard,

11:40.701 --> 11:42.569
cops haven't
arrested him yet.

11:42.603 --> 11:45.506
I'm not really following it
since he fired me and all.

11:45.539 --> 11:47.473
I'm talking about
the money you owe him.

11:47.508 --> 11:50.711
Oh, that. Yeah.

11:50.744 --> 11:52.979
We're in the past tense
on that.

11:53.013 --> 11:54.447
Definitely.

11:55.782 --> 11:57.050
Good.

12:14.234 --> 12:16.870
Death would be presumed
after seven years, Your Honor.

12:16.903 --> 12:18.639
Which means the statute
of limitations

12:18.672 --> 12:20.841
for wrongful death
has long since run.

12:20.874 --> 12:23.610
Unless there's fraud
that prevented the Baldwins

12:23.644 --> 12:25.979
from finding out that he
caused the wrongful death.

12:26.012 --> 12:27.313
HENRIETTA: There
wasn't any fraud.

12:27.347 --> 12:29.783
ELLENOR: John Pierce disappeared
days after kidnapping--

12:29.816 --> 12:31.084
HENRIETTA:
Allegedly kidnapping.

12:31.117 --> 12:33.754
He also assumed
a false name and identity--

12:33.787 --> 12:35.055
Alexander Wriat.

12:35.088 --> 12:38.525
That's fraud? Mr. Pierce
wanted a fresh start,

12:38.559 --> 12:39.793
to get out from
under the cloud

12:39.826 --> 12:42.228
of unfounded,
unjust suspicion.

12:42.262 --> 12:45.331
He was convicted of sex crimes
under this alias

12:45.365 --> 12:46.332
in another state.

12:46.366 --> 12:48.268
It took
the Baldwins' investigator

12:48.301 --> 12:51.705
to figure out that Pierce
and Wriat were one and the same.

12:51.738 --> 12:54.040
Why didn't your clients
at least file their lawsuit

12:54.074 --> 12:56.309
within the prescribed period
to preserve their claim?

12:56.342 --> 12:57.477
It would have been pointless

12:57.511 --> 12:59.613
since they couldn't locate
the defendant.

12:59.646 --> 13:01.214
You don't need to know
where a defendant is

13:01.247 --> 13:02.549
in order to file
a lawsuit.

13:02.583 --> 13:04.551
You do in order to serve him.

13:04.585 --> 13:06.352
He was found
three years later.

13:06.386 --> 13:08.221
They could have served him
in prison.

13:08.254 --> 13:11.758
All right. I'm going
to let the claim survive

13:11.792 --> 13:14.260
the statute of limitations
challenge,

13:14.294 --> 13:17.731
but as to whether there's
a case here at all,

13:17.764 --> 13:19.265
there wasn't even
enough evidence

13:19.299 --> 13:20.734
for the police
to make an arrest.

13:20.767 --> 13:22.636
Different standard of proof
in criminal cases.

13:22.669 --> 13:24.538
This is civil.
Oh, who's kidding who?

13:24.571 --> 13:27.007
If the police thought he had
kidnapped Chad Baldwin--

13:27.040 --> 13:28.775
The police did
and do think that.

13:28.809 --> 13:30.611
They're just unable
to prove it.

13:30.644 --> 13:32.112
And you think you can?

13:32.145 --> 13:34.447
I would like at least
to be allowed

13:34.480 --> 13:35.916
to conduct discovery.

13:39.986 --> 13:42.823
I'm going to grant you
a short evidentiary hearing.

13:42.856 --> 13:45.125
If you can make a showing
that you have anything

13:45.158 --> 13:47.928
worth submitting to a jury,
I'll let it stand.

13:47.961 --> 13:51.331
Otherwise, I'm granting
the defendant's motion.

13:51.364 --> 13:53.534
We'll see you back here
tomorrow, 10:00 a. m.

13:54.200 --> 13:56.302
Tomorrow?

13:56.336 --> 13:58.505
If you're not ready
to make a showing, counsel,

13:58.539 --> 14:02.442
after 18 years,
that certainly gives me pause.

14:02.475 --> 14:04.210
We'll be here.

14:04.244 --> 14:05.979
Put the defendant
back into custody.

14:19.359 --> 14:21.962
We just want
to give him a funeral.

14:21.995 --> 14:24.364
I will forgive you
if you just tell us where he is.
Jenny.

14:24.397 --> 14:25.732
Honey.
Mrs. Baldwin!

14:25.766 --> 14:27.701
Jenny, please.
Don't, don't.

14:27.734 --> 14:29.169
Please. Please.
Come on.

14:39.079 --> 14:40.581
I'm sorry.
It's all right.

14:40.614 --> 14:43.116
Okay, it's time to put up
or shut up.

14:43.149 --> 14:46.352
Do we have the transcripts
from the previous trials?
Lucy ordered them.

14:46.386 --> 14:48.288
Okay, Jenny,
you testify first.
Okay.

14:48.321 --> 14:49.890
You might be attacked
on memory,

14:49.923 --> 14:51.792
the fact that it happened
18 years ago.

14:51.825 --> 14:54.494
I've been playing it back
for 18 years, Mr. Donnell.

14:54.528 --> 14:56.329
I remember it
as if it was yesterday.

14:57.197 --> 14:58.231
Good.

15:10.310 --> 15:11.678
Hi, Jimmy.
How you doing?

15:11.712 --> 15:13.847
I asked you
not to come back here.

15:13.880 --> 15:15.616
Let's say I missed you.

15:17.083 --> 15:18.619
Take a
walk with me.

15:18.852 --> 15:19.620
Let's go.

15:35.235 --> 15:36.737
Is this all of it?

15:36.770 --> 15:39.205
I just gave you $14,800.

15:39.239 --> 15:41.474
Which I appreciate,
but you owe me 33.

15:41.508 --> 15:42.609
Twenty-seven.

15:42.643 --> 15:46.446
Thirty-three with
the juice-- 8.25 percent.

15:46.479 --> 15:48.615
This is every penny
I can get my hands on.

15:50.150 --> 15:51.785
Morris.

15:51.818 --> 15:53.887
What a surprise.
You know Jimmy Berluti?

15:56.923 --> 15:58.725
Look, Jimmy, I know
what you're thinking.

15:58.759 --> 15:59.860
Morris is a big guy.

15:59.893 --> 16:01.094
I brought him here
to rough you up

16:01.127 --> 16:03.530
just like in the movies,
right?

16:03.564 --> 16:06.032
Kind of cliche,
if you ask me.

16:06.066 --> 16:08.535
But... I tell you,

16:08.569 --> 16:11.237
whatever words people
might use to describe me...

16:12.338 --> 16:13.674
Uhh!

16:13.707 --> 16:15.441
(choking)

16:17.878 --> 16:20.581
..."original" isn't
one of them.

16:23.183 --> 16:26.553
Thirty-six hours--
I'll have the rest.

16:26.587 --> 16:28.388
You got till tomorrow.

16:35.495 --> 16:36.997
We just caught a break.
What?

16:37.030 --> 16:38.431
That was a guy
named Bud Reynolds.

16:38.464 --> 16:40.100
He's a resident
at state prison.

16:40.133 --> 16:41.968
He claims John Pierce
told him

16:42.002 --> 16:44.370
he kidnapped
the Baldwin boy.

16:44.404 --> 16:45.639
Becca, let's go.

16:49.943 --> 16:55.734
John Pierce confessed to you
he kidnapped, abused,
and killed Chad Baldwin?

16:56.016 --> 16:57.183
Yeah.

16:57.217 --> 16:59.085
After 18 years
of denying it,

16:59.119 --> 17:02.255
he suddenly tells
a stranger he did it?

17:02.288 --> 17:04.525
We weren't strangers.
We were friends.

17:04.558 --> 17:06.627
Which explains why
you're ratting on him.

17:06.660 --> 17:09.194
Hey, you don't got to
believe me.

17:09.229 --> 17:10.564
It's nothing to me.

17:11.431 --> 17:12.965
Why?
Why what?

17:12.999 --> 17:15.868
Why so public-spirited?
What's in it for you?

17:15.902 --> 17:19.105
That warm glow
you get right here

17:19.138 --> 17:21.575
when you squash a maggot.

17:21.608 --> 17:24.877
I said we were friends.
We're not now.

17:26.112 --> 17:28.815
When did this conversation
take place?

17:28.849 --> 17:31.217
Six, eight months ago.

17:32.118 --> 17:33.419
Why didn't you report it?

17:33.453 --> 17:35.055
Tell you the truth,

17:35.088 --> 17:37.724
I kept hoping somebody'd
stick a shank in his throat,

17:37.758 --> 17:40.460
but nobody ever did,
and he's getting out soon.

17:42.629 --> 17:45.498
How exactly did this
conversation come about?

17:46.332 --> 17:47.634
I don't remember.

17:47.668 --> 17:48.835
Just came up.

17:51.538 --> 17:53.974
Jailhouse informants
lie all the time.

17:54.007 --> 17:56.577
But to the police?
To cut a deal here?

17:56.610 --> 17:58.111
What would be his motive?

17:58.144 --> 17:59.846
Well, maybe just
to get a day in court,

17:59.880 --> 18:01.081
break up the week.

18:01.114 --> 18:02.549
Did he seem believable?

18:02.583 --> 18:04.518
I couldn't really tell.

18:05.385 --> 18:07.453
He's not asking
for anything,

18:07.487 --> 18:09.155
which makes me suspect

18:09.189 --> 18:10.791
he's probably
telling the truth.

18:13.927 --> 18:16.396
So he is dead.

18:16.429 --> 18:17.531
My son.

18:19.533 --> 18:20.734
Part of me thought...

18:22.302 --> 18:24.938
...he was really
still alive somewhere.

18:27.473 --> 18:29.075
Hoped, I guess.

18:32.278 --> 18:33.647
Did you arrange a transport?

18:34.781 --> 18:36.416
All taken care of.

18:36.449 --> 18:38.451
Okay, Jenny,
you're still up first.

18:39.419 --> 18:40.854
Then we'll call
this Reynolds guy.

18:55.135 --> 18:56.603
(sighs)

18:56.637 --> 19:00.240
Jeez, Jimmy, I told you,
the timing--

19:00.273 --> 19:02.242
Can you help me
with anything?

19:02.275 --> 19:03.644
A couple of thousand?

19:03.677 --> 19:06.647
It's killing me,
but I can't.

19:11.518 --> 19:12.686
You okay?

19:13.520 --> 19:14.821
You don't look good.

19:19.660 --> 19:21.562
Tell me about
this horse.

19:27.033 --> 19:28.434
We were at the park.

19:28.468 --> 19:30.203
We used to go
every morning.

19:30.236 --> 19:32.138
It was Chad's
favorite thing to do.

19:32.172 --> 19:34.040
BOBBY: What would
your son do there?

19:34.074 --> 19:36.777
JENNY: He loved constructing
things in the sandbox,

19:36.810 --> 19:38.779
I guess like
any four-year-old.

19:38.812 --> 19:41.014
This day he was playing
with his Legos.

19:41.047 --> 19:42.448
And what
were you doing?

19:42.482 --> 19:45.051
I was watching him,
as well as my daughter Susan,

19:45.085 --> 19:46.152
who was on the swings.

19:46.787 --> 19:47.721
Then what happened?

19:47.754 --> 19:49.923
Susan fell off a swing
and hurt herself,

19:49.956 --> 19:51.191
and she was crying.

19:51.224 --> 19:52.893
I ran over
to see about her.

19:53.727 --> 19:55.495
Maybe 30 or 40 seconds.

19:57.097 --> 20:00.233
And when I looked back,
Chad was gone.

20:00.266 --> 20:01.768
BOBBY: While your
son was playing,

20:01.802 --> 20:03.970
did you see anybody else
in the area?

20:04.571 --> 20:06.907
I saw that man.
John Pierce?

20:06.940 --> 20:08.675
Yes. He was
at a water fountain

20:08.709 --> 20:11.077
about 20 feet away
from where Chad was playing.

20:11.111 --> 20:12.245
What was he doing?

20:12.278 --> 20:14.314
Just standing there
watching the children.

20:14.347 --> 20:15.916
Did that make you nervous?

20:15.949 --> 20:17.818
I really didn't
think about it.

20:17.851 --> 20:22.022
Um, I had seen him before.

20:22.055 --> 20:23.624
And he always seemed
a little weird,

20:23.657 --> 20:25.559
but none of us--
the mothers--

20:25.592 --> 20:27.060
knew he was
a child molester.

20:27.093 --> 20:28.128
Objection.

20:28.161 --> 20:29.362
I'll ignore it.

20:29.395 --> 20:32.198
After you noticed that
your son was gone,

20:32.232 --> 20:33.767
did you see Mr. Pierce?

20:33.800 --> 20:35.936
No. He was gone, too.

20:35.969 --> 20:38.304
It all happened
in seconds.

20:38.338 --> 20:42.375
Mrs. Baldwin, did you see
anyone else nearby

20:42.408 --> 20:43.977
who could have disappeared
with Chad

20:44.010 --> 20:46.379
in a matter of seconds?

20:46.412 --> 20:47.981
No.
Thank you.

20:54.988 --> 20:57.858
I'm very sorry about the loss
of your son, Mrs. Baldwin.

20:57.891 --> 21:00.694
Yes, you told me that.

21:00.727 --> 21:03.597
Mr. Pierce actually
worked at park, didn't he?

21:03.630 --> 21:04.765
Evidently.

21:04.798 --> 21:06.667
You said he seemed weird.

21:06.700 --> 21:09.402
Had you ever complained
about him to anyone?

21:09.435 --> 21:10.671
No.

21:10.704 --> 21:12.305
To your knowledge,
did any of the mothers

21:12.338 --> 21:14.074
ever complain about
Mr. Pierce's behavior

21:14.107 --> 21:15.576
toward their children?

21:15.609 --> 21:17.043
Not to my knowledge.

21:17.077 --> 21:18.478
Did you ever see him behave

21:18.512 --> 21:20.647
in a scary
or inappropriate manner

21:20.681 --> 21:22.816
around the children?

21:22.849 --> 21:25.318
He stared at them
sometimes.

21:25.351 --> 21:27.554
You never did see him
abduct your son, did you?

21:27.588 --> 21:30.490
I didn't see it, but--
So it could have been
somebody else.

21:30.524 --> 21:31.992
Nobody else was near Chad.

21:32.025 --> 21:33.527
How do you know?

21:33.560 --> 21:35.596
If Mr. Pierce could
disappear into the trees,

21:35.629 --> 21:37.698
someone else could've
been hiding in there,
couldn't they?

21:37.731 --> 21:39.432
It was him.

21:41.502 --> 21:44.204
It helps to have
somebody to blame,

21:44.237 --> 21:46.306
doesn't it, Mrs. Baldwin,

21:46.339 --> 21:48.408
to give the monster
a face,

21:48.441 --> 21:51.077
even if it's the wrong face?
Objection.

21:51.111 --> 21:54.080
Withdrawn.
That's all I have.

22:39.526 --> 22:41.595
Are you authorized to make
withdrawals from this account?

22:41.628 --> 22:43.797
I'm a lawyer
with the firm.

22:43.830 --> 22:45.532
I'm James Berluti.

22:45.566 --> 22:47.534
I should be
on record here.

22:47.568 --> 22:49.102
The manager knows me.

22:49.135 --> 22:51.872
Mr. Berluti, I'll just
have to get this approved.

22:51.905 --> 22:53.373
Fifteen thousand?
Yes.

22:53.406 --> 22:55.275
Okay, it'll just
take a second.

23:11.357 --> 23:13.727
We found three Legos
in his apartment.

23:13.760 --> 23:15.796
Did John Pierce tell you
how they got there?

23:15.829 --> 23:17.197
Yes. He said he had them

23:17.230 --> 23:18.799
for when his nephews
came over.

23:18.832 --> 23:20.767
Three Legos?
Yes.

23:20.801 --> 23:23.469
Three lone Legos?
That's correct.

23:23.504 --> 23:26.973
Did you determine
how often his nephews,
in fact, came over?

23:27.240 --> 23:30.811
We determined
he had no nephews.

23:30.844 --> 23:33.146
Were you ever able
to determine that the Legos

23:33.179 --> 23:35.281
you found in
Mr. Pierce's apartment

23:35.315 --> 23:36.817
belonged to Chad Baldwin?

23:37.518 --> 23:38.685
No, we were not.

23:38.719 --> 23:40.386
Any evidence
of Chad Baldwin

23:40.420 --> 23:42.656
ever being present
in my client's apartment?

23:42.689 --> 23:43.624
No.

23:43.657 --> 23:45.726
Any physical, testimonial,

23:45.759 --> 23:47.794
or forensic evidence
to suggest

23:47.828 --> 23:51.732
that Chad Baldwin ever came
in contact with John Pierce?

23:51.765 --> 23:53.399
Only the testimony
of the mother,

23:53.433 --> 23:55.168
who said she saw him
close to her son.

24:00.406 --> 24:02.643
I wish I could be
more optimistic.

24:02.676 --> 24:04.377
What about
the informant?

24:04.410 --> 24:07.480
He's going up next,
but his credibility...

24:10.083 --> 24:12.986
the only other thing
I can think of is
to call Pierce.

24:14.020 --> 24:15.221
If he doesn't take
the Fifth,

24:15.255 --> 24:16.790
maybe if I go at him
hard enough,

24:16.823 --> 24:19.325
he'll say something
to incriminate himself.

24:19.359 --> 24:23.263
Contrary to the myth,
not all child molesters
are rocket scientists.

24:30.937 --> 24:32.539
ANNOUNCER: Race number
eight will begin

24:32.573 --> 24:34.340
in approximately 15 minutes.

24:34.374 --> 24:37.477
Please proceed to the betting
window to place your bet.

24:37.511 --> 24:40.380
Twelve thousand
on number four--

24:40.413 --> 24:43.183
Maddie's Charm to win.

24:43.216 --> 24:46.620
A hundred dollar exacta wheel,
