24:55.962 --> 24:58.098
ANNOUNCER: Your
attention please.

24:58.131 --> 25:00.601
The photo results
of the last race
are now available.

25:07.007 --> 25:09.342
Eugene, this just came
through the fax.

25:09.375 --> 25:10.811
It's...

25:10.844 --> 25:12.278
What?

25:12.312 --> 25:14.981
A CTR form from the bank.

25:15.015 --> 25:17.150
There's been a withdrawal
from the Peterson account.

25:24.958 --> 25:28.228
Before we move on
to what Mr. Pierce said to you,

25:28.261 --> 25:30.030
can you tell me
how you feel about him?

25:30.731 --> 25:32.533
I can't stand him.

25:32.566 --> 25:34.367
I make no bones there.

25:34.400 --> 25:36.169
Why don't you like
Mr. Pierce?

25:36.202 --> 25:38.572
He told the CO
I had contraband in my cell,

25:38.605 --> 25:40.440
and I got put
in the hole for a few days.

25:40.473 --> 25:41.975
What kind of contraband?

25:42.008 --> 25:43.844
A hot plate.

25:43.877 --> 25:46.547
Are you a vindictive person,
Mr. Reynolds?

25:46.580 --> 25:49.015
Are you testifying
to get back at the defendant?

25:49.049 --> 25:51.552
No. I just think
he deserves to go down

25:51.585 --> 25:53.219
for what he did
to that Baldwin boy.

25:53.820 --> 25:55.421
All right.

25:55.455 --> 25:58.792
What, exactly,
did he tell you about that?

25:58.825 --> 26:01.528
He said-- and this is
pretty much of a quote--

26:01.562 --> 26:03.764
"I sure did enjoy
getting that boy out

26:03.797 --> 26:05.866
from under
his mama's nose.

26:05.899 --> 26:07.467
He was a real looker."

26:07.500 --> 26:09.936
Did he say who
he was talking about?

26:09.970 --> 26:12.438
He said that kid who was
snatched from the park--

26:12.472 --> 26:14.775
Chad Baldwin,
the one on the news.

26:14.808 --> 26:19.012
Did he tell you
he murdered Chad?

26:19.045 --> 26:21.047
He didn't use that word.

26:21.081 --> 26:22.883
He said he cleaned up
after himself,

26:22.916 --> 26:25.786
and that he regretted not
keeping the kid around longer

26:25.819 --> 26:27.220
'cause he was good.

26:27.253 --> 26:29.823
What was his demeanor
as he was telling you this?

26:30.924 --> 26:32.058
Sort of dreamy.

26:33.527 --> 26:36.229
The same look a man gets
when he's remembering a woman.

26:37.898 --> 26:39.432
ANNOUNCER: The horses
are at the gate.

26:39.465 --> 26:42.068
It's post time
for the race.

26:42.102 --> 26:43.504
(bell rings)

26:43.537 --> 26:45.405
(announcer chattering)

26:47.273 --> 26:49.209
(cheering)

26:57.718 --> 27:00.286
HENRIETTA: Did he ever
give you any specific
details of this crime?

27:00.320 --> 27:01.855
Just what I told you.

27:01.888 --> 27:04.124
Just that he did it.
And enjoyed it.

27:04.157 --> 27:06.527
Isn't it true
that you told Mr. Pierce

27:06.560 --> 27:07.794
you were gonna
get even with him?

27:07.828 --> 27:09.195
No, it's not.

27:09.229 --> 27:11.397
What are you serving
a sentence for, Mr. Reynolds?

27:11.431 --> 27:13.499
Embezzlement and assault.

27:13.534 --> 27:16.036
So we can safely assume
you are both a dishonest

27:16.069 --> 27:18.038
and a violent person,
can we not?

27:18.071 --> 27:20.306
I am telling
the truth here.

27:20.340 --> 27:22.943
You even have a reputation
in prison for being
a snitch, don't you?

27:22.976 --> 27:23.910
Undeserved.

27:23.944 --> 27:26.012
Makes sense that
Mr. Pierce would confess

27:26.046 --> 27:28.014
to a known snitch, doesn't it?

27:28.048 --> 27:30.551
Well, I find
pedophiles lack judgment.

27:32.986 --> 27:35.388
(cheering)

27:36.389 --> 27:37.624
Move it!

27:37.658 --> 27:38.792
Move it, four!

27:38.825 --> 27:40.326
Come on, four, move it!

27:40.861 --> 27:42.162
Whip him, Jorge!

27:42.195 --> 27:43.930
Come on, Jorge, whip him, baby!

27:43.964 --> 27:45.799
Come on, baby!
Come on, four!

27:45.832 --> 27:47.200
Make your move, four!

27:47.233 --> 27:48.869
Run him, baby! Run him, baby!

27:48.902 --> 27:50.971
Get inside! Get inside!

27:51.004 --> 27:52.939
Go, baby, go! That's it!

27:52.973 --> 27:54.174
Come on now!

27:54.207 --> 27:56.643
Jorge, bring it around!
Bring it inside!

27:56.677 --> 27:58.545
Go home, baby!
Bring it home, four!

27:58.579 --> 28:00.614
Come on, four!
Come on, baby!

28:00.647 --> 28:02.282
Come on! Come on! Come on!

28:02.315 --> 28:03.684
Four! Four!

28:03.717 --> 28:06.019
Come on! Come on! Go! Go!

28:06.052 --> 28:07.420
Go! Go! Four!

28:07.453 --> 28:09.455
Four! Four!
Oh, come on, baby!

28:09.489 --> 28:11.157
Oh, come on, four!

28:11.191 --> 28:12.826
(screaming)

28:13.694 --> 28:15.328
(panting)

28:15.361 --> 28:16.830
(crowd cheering)

28:17.564 --> 28:18.665
I won.

28:24.037 --> 28:25.338
I won.

28:27.808 --> 28:29.475
Anything else, Mr. Donnell?

28:29.510 --> 28:32.779
Yes, Your Honor.
We call John Pierce
to the stand.

28:32.813 --> 28:35.315
Objection.
Mr. Donnell knows full well

28:35.348 --> 28:36.783
I'm not about
to allow that to happen.

28:36.817 --> 28:39.720
This is a civil proceeding.
I can call whoev--

28:39.753 --> 28:41.387
And if criminal charges
could follow,

28:41.421 --> 28:43.423
my client is allowed to assert
his Fifth Amendment right

28:43.456 --> 28:45.458
not to testify,
and my advice for him

28:45.491 --> 28:46.993
to do exactly that
won't be subtle.

28:47.027 --> 28:49.129
Given that 18 years
have passed,

28:49.162 --> 28:51.665
the likelihood that criminal
charges will be brought--

28:51.698 --> 28:54.000
We're not talking likelihoods.
There's still a chance.

28:54.034 --> 28:58.204
This man is a convicted
child molester.

28:58.238 --> 28:59.640
He was seen
and identified

28:59.673 --> 29:01.642
as being within 50 feet
of the victim

29:01.675 --> 29:03.443
at the time
of the kidnapping.

29:03.476 --> 29:06.713
Chad Baldwin was playing
with Legos at the time.

29:06.747 --> 29:09.415
Legos were found
in that bastard's apartment.

29:09.449 --> 29:11.351
Objection!
Mr. Donnell.

29:12.285 --> 29:14.988
We all know
we can't get him criminally.

29:15.021 --> 29:18.024
At least give us a chance
to get him civilly.

29:18.058 --> 29:19.192
Counsel, step up.

29:25.799 --> 29:27.534
First, Mr. Donnell,

29:27.568 --> 29:29.970
as much as I admire
your passion,

29:30.003 --> 29:32.773
you are not exactly known
as a champion of fair play,

29:32.806 --> 29:35.942
so I would delete
the moral indignation

29:35.976 --> 29:39.079
from your repertoire.

29:39.112 --> 29:42.583
Now, Ms. Lightstone.

29:42.616 --> 29:46.152
True, your client does not
have to testify here,

29:46.186 --> 29:49.089
but if he doesn't,
you might not like my finding.

29:49.122 --> 29:51.558
My client is judgment-proof.
I'm not terribly concerned--

29:51.592 --> 29:53.694
I am not talking
about civil liability.

29:53.727 --> 29:55.095
What are
you talking about?

29:55.128 --> 29:58.198
You're a good lawyer, Henrietta.
Figure it out.

29:58.231 --> 30:00.500
As a convicted pedophile,

30:00.534 --> 30:02.368
your client
can be kept in jail

30:02.402 --> 30:04.370
even after his sentence
has expired

30:04.404 --> 30:06.840
if he's considered
to be a danger to society.

30:06.873 --> 30:09.643
He has already satisfied
the psychiatrists that he's not.

30:09.676 --> 30:12.879
Yes. They consider him
to be rehabilitated,

30:12.913 --> 30:14.715
full of remorse.

30:14.748 --> 30:16.316
Well, from where I sit--

30:16.349 --> 30:18.652
and I tend to like
the view up here--

30:18.685 --> 30:20.486
I'm not getting that picture.

30:21.522 --> 30:24.357
If he refuses to testify,

30:24.390 --> 30:25.626
that makes me concerned

30:25.659 --> 30:28.061
as to whether
he has truly reformed.

30:28.094 --> 30:29.029
What are you saying?

30:29.062 --> 30:31.632
I want to hear from him.

30:31.665 --> 30:32.766
Otherwise,

30:32.799 --> 30:34.400
the District Attorney's office

30:34.434 --> 30:36.637
might want to bring
civil commitment proceedings,

30:36.670 --> 30:38.672
and your client
may never get out.

30:38.705 --> 30:40.206
This is blackmail.

30:40.240 --> 30:43.309
I'm just pointing
out risks, counsel.

30:43.343 --> 30:45.679
So if my client
refuses to testify,

30:45.712 --> 30:46.880
you can find him
uncooperative

30:46.913 --> 30:48.481
and recommend
he stay locked up forever,

30:48.515 --> 30:49.983
and if he testifies
and slips up,

30:50.016 --> 30:51.585
he could stay
locked up forever.

30:52.919 --> 30:54.187
Choose your poison.

31:02.095 --> 31:03.930
Now we have our leverage.

31:03.964 --> 31:06.967
He's got a strong incentive
to tell us where the body is

31:07.000 --> 31:08.068
if it'll stop this train.

31:08.101 --> 31:10.070
There's no way
they want to risk testifying.

31:10.103 --> 31:12.673
If he did testify,
do you think you could get him?

31:12.706 --> 31:14.741
I should be able to shake him
enough to give spindle doubts.

31:14.775 --> 31:16.577
That's what they have to
be afraid of now.

31:16.610 --> 31:19.279
He's not just risking
criminal prosecution.

31:19.312 --> 31:20.681
If he plays dodgeball
with me,

31:20.714 --> 31:22.683
the DA could argue
he's not rehabilitated

31:22.716 --> 31:24.818
and seek involuntary
confinement.

31:24.851 --> 31:27.453
It's civil,
but prison is prison.

31:27.487 --> 31:29.355
We got him
in the crossfire now.

31:29.389 --> 31:31.424
Our leverage is great.

31:31.457 --> 31:33.193
Now's the time
to go back to them.

31:33.226 --> 31:34.360
With what?

31:34.394 --> 31:36.396
Well, if he tells us
where the remains are,

31:36.429 --> 31:39.132
we drop our claim,
he gets his freedom...

31:41.101 --> 31:43.336
...and you get to have
a funeral for your son.

31:46.372 --> 31:47.508
No.

31:57.417 --> 31:59.886
Why not?
Jenny?

31:59.920 --> 32:00.987
What's wrong?

32:02.689 --> 32:05.726
Bobby, you asked us
at the beginning
why we hired you.

32:07.060 --> 32:08.729
And I gave you
an honest answer--

32:08.762 --> 32:11.932
that we wanted closure.

32:11.965 --> 32:13.033
BOBBY: And?

32:13.066 --> 32:16.236
And sitting here
right now...

32:16.269 --> 32:19.139
I don't know,
faced with the possibility
that he could go free,

32:19.172 --> 32:20.473
I suddenly realize...

32:21.542 --> 32:23.710
I want vengeance more.

32:23.744 --> 32:25.646
Jenny.
If the choice is

32:25.679 --> 32:27.480
get the body back
and he goes free

32:27.514 --> 32:30.383
versus don't get the body
and he rots in jail,

32:30.416 --> 32:32.018
I choose that he rots.

32:37.591 --> 32:38.825
Are you sure?

32:40.627 --> 32:42.162
I want him to rot.

32:52.873 --> 32:54.675
EUGENE: Jimmy.

32:54.708 --> 32:56.042
Can I see you
for a minute?

33:03.950 --> 33:05.251
Shut the door.

33:10.624 --> 33:11.692
What's up?

33:16.697 --> 33:19.465
Yeah, it's a withdrawal slip.
What about it?

33:22.302 --> 33:24.505
What do you need
$15,000 for?

33:26.372 --> 33:28.308
I had some expenses
on the Peterson case.

33:28.341 --> 33:30.343
You're not
a good liar, Jimmy.

33:30.376 --> 33:31.512
What's going on?

33:34.314 --> 33:35.849
Okay.

33:35.882 --> 33:38.652
I had a personal
emergency, all right?

33:38.685 --> 33:41.087
The money's already back.
I just came from the bank.

33:41.121 --> 33:44.057
So you think that's that.

33:47.460 --> 33:50.797
Look, Eugene,
I got in a jam with a bookie.

33:50.831 --> 33:52.733
I borrowed money
for, like, seven hours.

33:52.766 --> 33:54.367
You stole money.

33:54.400 --> 33:56.402
You took
from a client's trust fund.

33:56.436 --> 33:58.672
That's theft.

33:58.705 --> 34:02.442
I'm sorry. I-It was
a one-time situation.

34:02.475 --> 34:05.078
Can we just let it go?
No.

34:05.111 --> 34:06.913
We can't.

34:06.947 --> 34:08.849
This affects
the entire firm.

34:10.382 --> 34:11.585
I got to bring it
to Bobby.

34:11.618 --> 34:14.721
Please, just don't do that.
Please.

34:14.755 --> 34:17.489
Eugene, please.

34:32.706 --> 34:34.440
Oh, Jimmy.

34:35.341 --> 34:36.610
Eugene wants to see you.

34:54.460 --> 34:57.598
I paid it all back
within six hours,
plus interest.

34:57.631 --> 35:01.334
By law, we're required
to notify the client
and the Bar.

35:02.435 --> 35:03.804
You do that, I'm dead.

35:03.837 --> 35:06.139
If I don't, this whole firm
could get disbarred!

35:06.172 --> 35:08.041
Bobby, I could go to jail.

35:08.074 --> 35:09.042
Whose fault is that?

35:09.075 --> 35:11.377
Look, Bobby, I'm done.

35:11.411 --> 35:12.779
You've said that before.

35:12.813 --> 35:14.681
I'm done! You have my word.

35:14.715 --> 35:16.950
I'm supposed to risk
everybody's reputation,

35:16.983 --> 35:20.153
risk this firm,
on the word of an addict?

35:20.186 --> 35:24.457
I'm not an addict!

35:24.490 --> 35:25.992
I'm due in court.

35:26.960 --> 35:28.595
What's gonna happen?
I don't know.

35:41.007 --> 35:42.108
Thanks a lot.

35:47.914 --> 35:49.916
This affects everybody,
Jimmy.

35:52.285 --> 35:53.419
Try to get that.

36:04.330 --> 36:08.969
Mr. Pierce,
if you didn't kidnap
Chad Baldwin,

36:09.002 --> 36:10.003
who did?

36:10.036 --> 36:11.471
I do not know.

36:11.505 --> 36:12.539
Do you care?

36:12.573 --> 36:15.942
Of course I care,
but it wasn't me.

36:15.976 --> 36:17.978
You've already told a lie,
haven't you,

36:18.011 --> 36:19.279
on my second question?

36:19.312 --> 36:20.981
Objection.
Sustained.

36:21.014 --> 36:24.484
You cared when Chad Baldwin
was kidnapped?

36:24.518 --> 36:27.988
Mr. Donnell,
I had a sexual problem

36:28.021 --> 36:31.357
for which I received both
treatment and medication,

36:31.391 --> 36:35.228
but I have never been
a person without compassion.

36:35.261 --> 36:37.363
BOBBY: So when
a four-year-old disappears,

36:37.397 --> 36:39.733
you would feel compassion.

36:39.766 --> 36:40.801
Yes.

36:40.834 --> 36:43.504
Would you bother to help
if you could?

36:44.270 --> 36:45.706
Because I'm curious.

36:45.739 --> 36:49.042
You were there at the time,
seen less than 50 feet away,

36:49.075 --> 36:50.911
you even knew the victim.

36:50.944 --> 36:52.412
Why didn't you go forward
to the police

36:52.445 --> 36:54.047
as a possible witness?

36:54.080 --> 36:56.482
Because I didn't see
anything.

36:56.517 --> 36:57.951
How do you know?

36:57.984 --> 37:01.187
Maybe there was something you
saw seemingly irrelevant to you,

37:01.221 --> 37:03.757
but it could've provided
a clue to them.

37:03.790 --> 37:06.793
Why didn't you at least say,
"Hey, how can I help?"

37:06.827 --> 37:10.531
Look, I was afraid
they'd suspect me.

37:10.564 --> 37:12.065
Why?

37:12.098 --> 37:14.367
At this point,
your record was clean.

37:14.400 --> 37:16.136
Why would they suspect you?

37:16.169 --> 37:18.438
You didn't molest those other
three boys till after.

37:18.471 --> 37:20.173
Objection.
Sustained.

37:20.206 --> 37:22.108
Your work shift
went to 4:00 p. m.,

37:22.142 --> 37:24.745
but I see, on this day,
you left early.

37:24.778 --> 37:27.247
I didn't feel well.
You didn't feel well.

37:27.280 --> 37:29.816
Did you go to a supervisor
to say you were leaving?

37:29.850 --> 37:31.985
No. I just went home.

37:32.018 --> 37:34.555
Coincidentally, you left
within 30 to 40 seconds

37:34.588 --> 37:37.524
of the time
Chad Baldwin disappeared.

37:37.558 --> 37:40.260
Can you account
for such a coincidence?

37:40.293 --> 37:42.963
A soon-to-be-convicted
child molester

37:42.996 --> 37:45.298
is within 50 feet
of a child

37:45.331 --> 37:47.968
at the exact time
he's kidnapped?

37:48.001 --> 37:50.604
Objection!
Withdrawn.

37:50.637 --> 37:51.805
Why did you leave
the state?

37:51.838 --> 37:54.307
I cooperated completely
with the police

37:54.340 --> 37:55.876
before I left the state.

37:55.909 --> 37:57.243
Why did you leave, sir?

37:57.277 --> 38:00.280
Because I expected
to get the same bias

38:00.313 --> 38:02.382
from everybody
that I'm getting from you.

38:02.415 --> 38:04.417
So you ran.
Yes.

38:04.450 --> 38:07.320
Tell us about those Legos.
Why'd you tell the police

38:07.353 --> 38:09.990
the Legos were for nephews
you didn't have?

38:10.023 --> 38:13.760
I lied.
As I said, I knew they
thought that I was guilty.

38:13.794 --> 38:16.663
So you lied.
Yes.

38:16.697 --> 38:18.932
Why didn't you tell them
the truth?

38:18.965 --> 38:22.869
Because I didn't remember
when I got the Legos.

38:22.903 --> 38:24.938
So you decided to say
you had nephews.

38:24.971 --> 38:25.939
Yes.

38:26.406 --> 38:28.642
What happened
to Chad Baldwin?

38:28.675 --> 38:30.010
I don't know.

38:30.043 --> 38:31.111
Do you care?

38:31.144 --> 38:33.479
I said, I care.

38:33.514 --> 38:36.482
Because you have compassion.

38:36.517 --> 38:40.020
Can you feel for his parents
sitting over there?

38:40.053 --> 38:42.355
Yes!
Can you understand
how they would love

38:42.388 --> 38:43.557
to get their son's remains

38:43.590 --> 38:45.526
so they can get
some kind of closure?

38:45.559 --> 38:47.661
Can you understand that?
Yes.

38:47.694 --> 38:49.896
Would you be willing
to help them if you could?

38:49.930 --> 38:51.497
Yes, but I can't.

38:51.532 --> 38:56.402
Well, even peace of mind that
you didn't take their son--

38:56.436 --> 38:58.104
would you be willing
to give them that?

38:58.138 --> 39:01.007
I'm trying right now.
I appreciate that.

39:01.041 --> 39:03.176
Would you be willing
to take a polygraph?

39:03.209 --> 39:04.811
Objection.
I'm not talking about

39:04.845 --> 39:07.080
using it for criminal purposes.

39:07.113 --> 39:09.516
A private polygraph
just between parties,

39:09.550 --> 39:14.621
just to satisfy my clients
that you didn't take their son.

39:14.655 --> 39:17.457
Would you be willing to do that
so they can just move on?

39:17.490 --> 39:19.726
Those things
aren't foolproof.

39:19.760 --> 39:22.262
Understood.
Would you be willing?

39:22.295 --> 39:24.297
I don't care if he's willing.
I won't allow it.

39:24.330 --> 39:27.500
Whatever your lawyer advises
or recommends,

39:27.534 --> 39:30.804
John, it's ultimately
your decision.

39:31.972 --> 39:34.474
Will you take
that polygraph?

39:34.508 --> 39:35.542
No.

39:35.576 --> 39:38.545
Because I don't trust them
to be reliable.

39:39.713 --> 39:42.015
And you insist
on reliability.

39:42.048 --> 39:43.383
HENRIETTA: Objection!

39:45.051 --> 39:46.186
Nothing further.

39:50.123 --> 39:51.958
All right, Mr. Pierce,
you may step down.

39:53.660 --> 39:55.796
Mr. Donnell,
any other witnesses?

39:55.829 --> 39:57.631
No, Your Honor.
Ms. Lightstone?

39:57.664 --> 39:59.465
No, but I'd like
to be heard.

39:59.499 --> 40:00.667
I'm not interested.

40:01.902 --> 40:03.737
All right.

40:03.770 --> 40:06.039
If the defendant
was not involved

40:06.072 --> 40:08.374
in the disappearance
of Chad Baldwin,

40:08.408 --> 40:12.813
then we have to assume
there was another
skulking child molester

40:12.846 --> 40:15.081
who happened to be hiding
behind a tree

40:15.115 --> 40:17.150
in the same area
at the same time.

40:18.785 --> 40:22.022
Mr. Pierce, you look
pretty guilty to me.

40:22.055 --> 40:24.791
But as for evidence,
that's all there is.

40:24.825 --> 40:26.927
You were there
at the time and place.

40:26.960 --> 40:29.262
Admittedly, your job required
you to be there.

40:31.765 --> 40:33.399
I'm gonna let this case
go forward,

40:33.433 --> 40:36.269
but, Mr. Donnell,
if you don't come up with more,

40:36.302 --> 40:38.338
I will be dismissing it
at a later date.

40:38.371 --> 40:39.773
What about recommending

40:39.806 --> 40:41.207
to the District Attorney's
Office

40:41.241 --> 40:42.843
that they file
for civil commitment?

40:45.411 --> 40:47.013
I can't recommend
a man's freedom

40:47.047 --> 40:49.516
be taken away
based on suspicion alone.

40:51.217 --> 40:52.553
We're adjourned.

41:05.532 --> 41:06.700
I'm sorry.

41:07.901 --> 41:09.970
Is it over?

41:10.003 --> 41:12.205
No. If the wrongful death
action survives,

41:12.238 --> 41:14.775
we can keep digging,

41:14.808 --> 41:17.410
but there's no money
to be won.

41:17.443 --> 41:19.045
And as for keeping him
in jail

41:19.079 --> 41:21.882
or finding the whereabouts
of your son's remains...

41:24.050 --> 41:25.151
...we struck out.

41:27.821 --> 41:29.322
I'm very sorry.

41:29.355 --> 41:31.357
You did your best.

41:31.391 --> 41:32.492
Perhaps a wiser lawyer

41:32.526 --> 41:34.895
would've steered you away
from all this.

41:35.696 --> 41:37.764
We wouldn't let you.

41:37.798 --> 41:38.999
You tried.

42:02.756 --> 42:04.124
Mr. Donnell?

42:04.157 --> 42:05.291
Yes.

42:05.325 --> 42:07.594
I'm James Tucker,
and this is my mother.

42:09.763 --> 42:10.964
How can I help you?

42:10.997 --> 42:13.199
We've been following
the Pierce trial in the news,

42:13.233 --> 42:15.669
and we need to talk
to somebody.

42:16.637 --> 42:17.804
About what?

42:20.907 --> 42:22.576
I think I may be
Chad Baldwin.

42:33.053 --> 42:34.655
TV ANNOUNCER: Hakim is
back to receive

42:34.688 --> 42:37.658
Hakim has had a problem
holding on to the ball.

42:40.426 --> 42:42.262
Both last year and
in pre-season,

42:42.295 --> 42:43.964
really one of the best
in the league.

42:43.997 --> 42:45.498
Tremendous kick.

42:45.532 --> 42:48.301
Hakim fields it back
at the 15 yard line...

42:49.803 --> 42:52.573
Hakim and only
the punter to beat!

42:52.606 --> 42:54.007
And knocked him down!

42:54.040 --> 42:56.242
He'll go all the way
for a touchdown!

42:56.276 --> 42:58.745
The punter was...

42:58.779 --> 43:00.714
No way!

43:00.747 --> 43:02.516
(crowd roaring)

43:30.110 --> 43:32.946
(music playing)

43:56.502 --> 43:57.538
You stinker!
